<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-22T17:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-22T17:16:00-05:00" n="229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/99: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-22T18:00:00-04:16"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                        1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    July 23, 1.05 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President signed this afternoon the contract for the laying of the
                            cable from Argentina to Uruguay authorized by the concession granted the
                            Central and South America Telegraph Company August 1, 1918.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>